    "is_good_patch": false,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix TLV length validation in NFAPI system information unpacking\n\n### Summary\nThe NB-IoT system information indication unpacking function in the NFAPI layer was not properly validating TLV length fields against the expected data size. This could lead to buffer overreads when malformed messages were received from the PNF.\n\nThe issue was caused by missing validation checks that ensure the TLV length field matches the expected size based on the sib_length value pulled from the data stream. When these values didn't match, subsequent processing could read beyond the end of the buffer.\n\nThis fix adds proper length validation to all system information unpacking functions to detect and reject malformed TLV structures before they can cause memory access violations.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p4.c`: Added TLV length validation in unpack_lte_system_information_indication_value\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p4.c`: Added TLV length validation in unpack_nb_iot_system_information_indication_value  \n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p4.c`: Added TLV length validation in unpack_utran_system_information_indication_value\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p4.c`: Added TLV length validation in unpack_geran_system_information_indication_value\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce this issue:\n1. Send a malformed NB-IoT system information indication message with a TLV length field that doesn't match the expected size based on the sib_length value\n2. The unpack_nb_iot_system_information_indication_value function will process the mismatched lengths\n3. This can cause buffer overreads when pullarray8 attempts to read more data than is actually present in the buffer\n4. Symptoms include segmentation faults or corrupted data processing downstream in the NGAP interface handling\n\nThe fix prevents this by checking that value->tl.length == (3 + value->sib_length) for NB-IoT/LTE messages and value->tl.length == (2 + data_length) for UTRAN/GERAN messages before proceeding with unpacking.\n"
}